page.title: 10School Projects
page.content: Yesterday we all got up at 7.30 am.I put on my swimming costumeand my clothes over the top. Then we put the dogs in the carand went to Houghton Regis swimming pool. We swim there on Sunday morning and Dad plays badminton.I start at 8.45 and Emma starts at 9.45. When I got out of the pool Mum came in the changing rooms and said that she was going to take Sooty and Fred(the dogs) for a walk.When I was dressed I watched Emma swimming,and had a packet of crisps. We went home and Mum and I cooked breakfast.We had eggs, fried bread, tomatoes and bacon. Emma and I played tennis and badminton.We went to watch a cricket match in Markyate. This was my family Sunday on 12th May 1985. Vicki Roch
